    "Fok and Weld (2023) argue that using the predictions is viable in this case.",
    "However, a worse model should not be chosen when a better-performing one is available and resource-appropriate.",
    "Finetuning large language models (LLMs) is an effective method for specializing a model to a task.",
    "We do so for each ⋆ task that fulfills all the criteria in §3.1 and quality checks.",
    "We use Flan-T5-3B (Wei et al., 2022) due to its size and versatility stemming from instruction finetuning with data of 1.8K tasks."
  ],
